alloc::collections::BTreeMap::<K, V>::ne.doc:
Makes a new, empty `BTreeMap`.

Does not allocate anything on its own.

# Examples

```
use std::collections::BTreeMap;

let mut map = BTreeMap::new();

// entries can now be inserted into the empty map
map.insert(1, "a");
```

